cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a large-scale dataset for machine learning approaches to MR image reconstruction, which suggests it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of machine learning also suggests it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The dataset includes both raw MR measurements and clinical MR images, which suggests it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
